# **🇬🇧 ENGLISH**  

## **📜 Code of Conduct**  
<img src="https://www.vectorlogo.zone/logos/opensource/opensource-icon.svg" width="30" align="left">  
We adhere to the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/). By participating, you agree to uphold this code.  
**Violations?** Contact: `email@example.com`.  

---

## **🚀 How to Contribute**  
### **1. 🐛 Reporting Bugs**  
<img src="https://www.vectorlogo.zone/logos/bugcrowd/bugcrowd-icon.svg" width="25" align="left">  
- Search [existing issues](https://github.com/yourusername/dotfile/issues) first.  
- Use the **Bug Report Template** and include:  
  ```markdown
  ### Environment  
  - OS: [e.g., macOS 14]  
  - Shell: [e.g., zsh 5.9]  
  ### Steps to Reproduce  
  1. ...  
  ### Expected vs Actual Behavior  
  ```  

### **2. 💡 Feature Requests**  
<img src="https://www.vectorlogo.zone/logos/google_chrome/google_chrome-icon.svg" width="25" align="left">  
- Tag with `enhancement` and provide:  
  - **Use case** (why is this valuable?).  
  - **Mockups** (Figma/SVG links preferred).  

### **3. 🛠 Pull Requests**  
<img src="https://www.vectorlogo.zone/logos/github/github-icon.svg" width="25" align="left">  
- Branch naming: `feat/description` or `fix/issue-number`.  
- **Tests required** for new features.  
- Update `CHANGELOG.md` (if applicable).  

---

## **⚙️ Development Setup**  
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/dotfile.git  
cd dotfile && npm install  # or other package manager  
```

---

## **🎨 Style Guide**  
| Category       | Rule                          |  
|----------------|-------------------------------|  
| **Variables**  | `lower_snake_case`            |  
| **Functions**  | `lowerCamelCase`              |  
| **Commits**    | Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org) |  

---

# **🇪🇸 ESPAÑOL**  

## **📜 Código de Conducta**  
<img src="https://www.vectorlogo.zone/logos/opensource/opensource-icon.svg" width="30" align="left">  
Seguimos el [Pacto de Colaboradores](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/es/). Cualquier violación debe reportarse a `email@example.com`.  

---

## **🚀 Cómo Contribuir**  
### **1. 🐛 Reportar Errores**  
<img src="https://www.vectorlogo.zone/logos/bugcrowd/bugcrowd-icon.svg" width="25" align="left">  
- Busca en [issues existentes](https://github.com/yourusername/dotfile/issues).  
- Usa la **Plantilla de Bugs** e incluye:  
  ```markdown
  ### Ambiente  
  - SO: [ej. Ubuntu 22.04]  
  - Shell: [ej. bash 5.1]  
  ### Pasos para Reproducir  
  1. ...  
  ```  

### **2. 💡 Solicitar Funcionalidades**  
<img src="https://www.vectorlogo.zone/logos/google_chrome/google_chrome-icon.svg" width="25" align="left">  
- Etiqueta con `enhancement` y provee:  
  - **Caso de uso** (¿por qué es útil?).  
  - **Bocetos** (preferible en SVG/Figma).  

### **3. 🛠 Pull Requests**  
<img src="https://www.vectorlogo.zone/logos/github/github-icon.svg" width="25" align="left">  
- Nombra ramas: `feat/descripción` o `fix/issue-número`.  
- **Pruebas obligatorias** para nuevas features.  
- Actualiza `CHANGELOG.md` (si aplica).  

---

## **⚙️ Configuración de Desarrollo**  
```bash
git clone https://github.com/tuusuario/dotfile.git  
cd dotfile && npm install  # u otro gestor de paquetes  
```

